o  .","Spanish and Portuguese: old personal name corresponding to   Velasco  ."]}]},{"name":"Teresa","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Theresa .  In the English-speaking world the name is often chosen in this spelling by Roman Catholics, with particular reference to the Spanish saint, Teresa of Ávila (  Teresa Cepeda de Ahumada ,  1515–82 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Theresa","meanings":["Of problematic origin. The name seems to have been first used in Spain and Portugal, and, according to tradition, was the name of the wife of St Paulinus of Nola, who spent most of his life in Spain; she was said to have originated (and to have derived her name) from the Greek island of <i>Thēra</i>. However, this story is neither factually nor etymologically confirmed."]},{"name":"Teresia","meanings":["form of   Theresa .  In the English-speaking world the name is often chosen in this spelling by Roman Catholics, with particular reference to the Spanish saint, Teresa of Ávila (  Teresa Cepeda de Ahumada ,  1515–82 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Teresa Vasques was born about 1144, in Portugal. She had at least 1 daughter with Rui Pires de Gandarei. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"aproximadamente 1144–":"umbes 1144–Surnud","1143–Male":"1143–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1144–Female":"1144–Surnud","aproximadamente 1144":"umbes 1144","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1144":"1144","1143":"1143","1180":"1180","Portugal":"Portugal"},"fi":{"aproximadamente 1144–":"noin 1144–Kuollut","1143–Male":"1143–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1144–Female":"1144–Kuollut","aproximadamente 1144":"noin 1144","about 1180":"noin 1180","1144":"1144","1143":"1143","1180":"1180","Portugal":"Portugali"},"fr":{"aproximadamente 1144–":"environ 1144–Décédée","1143–Male":"1143–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1144–Female":"1144–Décédée","aproximadamente 1144":"environ 1144","about 1180":"environ 1180","1144":"11